timelineItems.name: Jeremy Berg
timelineItems.text: 1-0 #SKC http://t.co/koJWK6jScp

timelineItems.name: Joel Hoover
timelineItems.text: Peter Vermes spoke very highly of Nemeth coming into this season. He is paying big dividends for them thus far. #SKC

timelineItems.name: Clayton Everett
timelineItems.text: Nemeth looked on the wrong side of hedges when that ball was played back across the goal #SKCvDAL

timelineItems.name: Univision Deportes
timelineItems.text: #UDMLS: Mira cómo fue el gol de Nemeth que abrió el marcador en el #SKCvDAL. http://t.co/Z4BWZFvsni

timelineItems.name: Prost Amerika
timelineItems.text: SKC passing well. Slowly getting better game by game. Some good selection posers lie ahead for Vermes when injured guys return. #SKCvDAL

timelineItems.name: 1020 Cawlidge Sports
timelineItems.text: 2' Connor Hallisey getting his first career start here tonight and makes a great defensive play early. #SKCvDAL

timelineItems.name: SKC Gameday
timelineItems.text: 3' Nemeth picks out Hallisey making a run down the right side, and the rookie wins SKC a corner in front of the Cauldron. #SKCvDAL

timelineItems.name: Orlando's Locos
timelineItems.text: That Watson boy fast! #SKCvFCD #SKCvDAL If Perez was that fast we'd be 1-1

timelineItems.name: Andy Edwards
timelineItems.text: #FCDallas midfield getting straight worked by #SportingKC right now, unable to find Diaz with any sort of space/time on the ball. #SKCvFCD

timelineItems.name: Jason Poon
timelineItems.text: Dear #FCDallas, please play to the whistle. Especially when the ball is definitely still in play. Thank you.

timelineItems.desc: Attempt missed. Krisztian Nemeth (Sporting Kansas City) right footed shot from outside the box is close, but misses to the left.
timelineItems.title: CHANCE: Krisztian Nemeth's effort goes just wide after great lead-up play

timelineItems.name: Kylee Renollet
timelineItems.text: Dallas' coach has the smallest arms I have ever seen on a man. #SKCvDAL

timelineItems.name: Tim Donahoe
timelineItems.text: #SKCvDAL #MLS Why does Pareja start Bekker over Michel? Won't they need someone to deliver set piece balls?

timelineItems.name: Andrew Wiebe
timelineItems.text: This Kristian Nemeth fella is lively, huh? #SKCvDAL

timelineItems.desc: Second yellow card to Zach Loyd (FC Dallas) for a bad foul.
timelineItems.title: RED CARD: Zach Loyd is sent off for a second yellow card in the first half

timelineItems.name: SKC Gameday
timelineItems.text: Neither side has posted a shutout in any of the last seven regular season meetings between @SportingKC and @FCDallas. #SKCvDAL

timelineItems.name: Justin
timelineItems.text: And now for the Benny show #SKCvDAL

timelineItems.name: SKC Gameday
timelineItems.text: Fabian Castillo is tied for 3rd in MLS with 5 assists and leads the league with 47 dribbles completed, 7 more than any other player #SKCvDAL

timelineItems.name: SKC Gameday
timelineItems.text: GK Dan Kennedy is winless in his last four games against #SportingKC (0-3-1) after winning his first two in 2008 and 2010. #SKCvDAL

timelineItems.name: Inside MLS
timelineItems.text: FC Dallas up against it now. Down a goal to Nemeth's opener. Down a man after Loyd procures second booking for hauling Nemeth down. #SKCvDAL

timelineItems.name: Brad Kirsopp
timelineItems.text: Zusi has also impressed in the first half, hope to see him return to his best form #SKCvDAL #SportingKC

timelineItems.name: Matt Pollard
timelineItems.text: This was the game that Mauro had to step up and make something happen for his team. Hasn't done enough so far tonight. #SKCvDAL

timelineItems.name: Sarah Lerner
timelineItems.text: Nemeth is really impressing me tonight. #SKCvDAL

timelineItems.name: Prost Amerika
timelineItems.text: Nemeth just beginning to play like his resume. Could be a dark horse for later individual season honors #SKCvDAL

timelineItems.name: Andy Edwards
timelineItems.text: Great first-half performance from #SportingKC, but as always, desperately need that 2nd goal. #FCDallas quick to bunker after an equalizer.

timelineItems.name: Kym Miller
timelineItems.text: Is it wrong that I'm already worried about Uri-level heartbreak when it comes to Nemeth? Should I start preparing myself? #SKCvFCD #SKC

timelineItems.name: Eric Lee
timelineItems.text: Olivia is loving her first @SportingKC game. #SKCvFCD #SKC http://t.co/TdCskpZQgV

timelineItems.name: SKC Gameday
timelineItems.text: Tonight is the second straight match in which @SportingKC has allowed zero shots on goal in the first half. 1-0 #SKCvDAL

timelineItems.name: Jason Poon
timelineItems.text: To get a point out of this #FCDallas needs to dip into last year's tactics of counter and set pieces. Barrios and Michel then?

timelineItems.text: This once cobbled together defense has been impressing the hell out of me. #SKCvDAL #SKC

timelineItems.name: Prost Amerika
timelineItems.text: With key players missing, SKC have sent out statements of intent to Seattle and Dallas in successive weeks. Next 4 also v West #SKCvDAL

timelineItems.name: Jonathan Campos
timelineItems.text: Dallas is getting turn up!! #MLSSAP

timelineItems.name: Ed Rowe
timelineItems.text: Hallisey's back pass to Zusi was awesome. #SKC

timelineItems.name: Kyle McCarthy
timelineItems.text: Sporting Kansas City rampant even before Loyd's dismissal. Impressive display. FCD pondering Friday boycotts next season. #SKCvDAL #MLS

timelineItems.name: Jason Poon
timelineItems.text: #FCDallas went for it when it was 2-0 to try and get a result. Can't fault them for trying. Was a gutsy move from Oscar that didn't pay off.

timelineItems.name: JeffreyL
timelineItems.text: I feeling a certain amount of elevated expectation from this lineup. Even without Castillo. #optimism #DTID #FCDallas

timelineItems.name: Josh Lentz
timelineItems.text: Yes Dallas is down a man, but this is still the most fluid and put together Sporting has looked all season #SKCvDAL

timelineItems.name: Jesse Gilmore
timelineItems.text: Zusi getting back into form just in time for Nemeth to leave for June friendlies. He will be missed. #SKCvDAL

timelineItems.name: SKC Gameday
timelineItems.text: 7' Feilhaber whips it into the middle of the penalty area and Hedges clears without much trouble. #SKCvDAL

timelineItems.name: Jason Poon
timelineItems.text: At this point I'd settle for forcing Melia to make a save. #FCDallas

timelineItems.name: Michael Letcher
timelineItems.text: Barney's all alone in the backfield, down 1 man. SKC 4, FCD 0 #SKCvDAL #SportingKC http://t.co/nyK16AnldM

timelineItems.name: Andy Edwards
timelineItems.text: Not to put a damper on the "we're gonna win the league" tweets I'm seeing, but #FCDallas are really pretty average w/o Castillo. #SportingKC

timelineItems.name: Jesse Gilmore
timelineItems.text: It will be interesting to see whose shoulders the #SKC scoring burden will rest upon once the June friendlies roll around. SEA, RSL, COL
